[[Amherst Central High School (Amherst, New York)|Amherst Central High School]], the town's public high school, is located at 4301 Main Street, just west of the business district.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.amherstschools.org/HighSchool.cfm|title=High School|accessdate=2009-04-09|publisher=Amherst Central Schools}}</ref>  The school started when the new Amherst school district was created in the late 1920s.<ref>Grande, p. 69</ref>  Previously students from Eggertsville and Snyder either attended [[Bennett High School (Buffalo, New York)|Bennett High School]] at 2885 Main Street in Buffalo or what is now called [[Williamsville South High School]] at 5950 Main Street in Williamsville and is listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] as Williamsville Junior and Senior High School.<ref>Grande, p. 82</ref>

[[Daemen College]] is located across from the high school at 4380 Main Street.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.daemen.edu/default.php|title=Daemen College|accessdate=2009-04-09|publisher=[[Daemen College]]}}</ref>  Amherst Middle School (formerly Amherst Junior High School), the town's public middle school, is located two blocks south of the High School at 55 Kings Highway.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.amherstschools.org/middleschool.cfm|title=Middle School|accessdate=2009-04-09|publisher=Amherst Central Schools}}</ref>  Additionally, the Stenograhic Institute-Western New York at 4525 Main Street, which offers undergraduate degrees,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.educationhq.org/college-195836.php|title=Stenograhic Institute-western New York|accessdate=2009-05-01|publisher=EducationHQ.org}}</ref> is found in the business district.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uscollegesearch.org/stenograhic-institutewestern-new-york.html|title=Stenograhic Institute-western New York|accessdate=2009-04-11|publisher=U.S. College Search}}</ref>

Other schools located in the district include Smallwood Drive Elementary School (K-5),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.amherstschools.org/smallwood.cfm|title=Smallwood|accessdate=2009-04-09|publisher=Amherst Central Schools}}</ref> Park School of Buffalo (Pre-K-12),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theparkschool.org/|title=The Park School|accessdate=2009-04-09|publisher=The Park Schools}}</ref> and Christ The King School (Pre-K-8).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ctksnyder.org/|title=Church of Christ the King|accessdate=2009-04-09|publisher=Church of Christ the King|author=Valone, Jan}}</ref> Park has been located in Snyder since 1922.<ref>Grande, p. 81</ref>  Smallwood is public; Park is private and Christ The King is a [[Roman Catholic]] school.

